It would be nice if /commits and /changesets were interchangeable in URLs. This would be nice for Git users who aren&#x27;t necessarily familiar with the term "changeset". It might be a good idea to have /commits URLs redirect to their canonical counterparts:

{{{\\
/user/repo/commits         -> /user/repo/changesets\\
/user/repo/commit/hash     -> /user/repo/changeset/hash\\
}}}

While you&#x27;re at it, these redirects are worth considering:

{{{\\
/user/repo/commits/hash    -> /user/repo/changeset/hash\\
/user/repo/changesets/hash -> /user/repo/changeset/hash\\
}}}
